data.title: Quick dinner
data.text: Ordered a little bit of everything. Started with tempura battered veggies, nice light batter and fresh vegetables. Then had three different sushi rolls, sweet potato very interesting but worth the try, the spot roll deep fried so worth it if you like a warm sushi roll and the Long Beach with soft shell crab. Last had a noodle vegetable plate. All in all was good. I usually would order some sashimi or rolls with raw fish but not truly knowing anything about the place didn't want to roll that dice. Would visit again. Service was great.

data.title: Decent Place for Sushi and More
data.text:
Nice newer restaurant.  There is a sushi bar, and another bar for  drinks. Not a large place, and can get loud when busy. It's been a while since I have had the same server. Thankfully service here has been okay. 

Try some of the traditional dishes as they're a nice break from the typical sushi. 

There is street parking and open lots nearby.

data.title: Mouth Watering Roll
data.text: Wow, wow and more wow... Service quick and happy, happy service is the key, it says I like working here.  Had Tiger, Alaskan and Salmon Avocado rolls.  Was so good we ordered a Mouth Watering roll by recommendation of the owner. Presentation 10. Wonderful food, wonderful staff, wonderful restaurant.

data.title: great array of choices here
data.text: As a fan of sushi restaurants in the past cities I've lived, I am extremely grateful there is Ninja in Eau Claire where I can go and have a dragon roll when I crave such a thing...

data.title: Sloth Carry-out
data.text: I ordered sushi carryout online. No time recommendation provided via the website. I arrive 25 minutes later, and proceed to wait 40 minutes for a few sushi rolls. If you're looking for sushi to-go, call ahead or go somewhere else. Sushi wasn't disappointing, however, the egg rolls were cold by the time I got home. Bartender was great, but management needs to get it together

data.title: Great quick lunch
data.text: Fairly extensive menu.  Service was fast and friendly, although a bit unpolished.  Everything we had was delicious.  The hot and sour soup was excellent and is almost a meal on its own.  Prices very reasonable.  We went for a couples lunch but plan to take our teenagers back for dinner soon.

data.title: Great place downtown
data.text: One more reason to go downtown. We have visited twice now and both times were great.  Food is wonderful and service is great. We love ordering the sushi rolls and sharing. Decor and atmosphere is perfect for the location. There is a small bar area along one end of the restaurant with TVs for the sports nut who can't go 10 minutes without a TV.  Parking can be an issue downtown but there is street parking and two parking ramps within 2 blocks. If you are staying at the Lismore or newly opened Oxbow Hotel it is a short walk from the hotels.

data.title: Great find with delicious food and beautiful plate presentation!
data.text: This place was recommended to us by the desk clerk at our hotel.  Parking was not convenient for us as we have a 4 door truck with a long bed and the parallel parking spots are for smaller vehicles.  It is a younger crowd due to the college area.  We had the General Tso's and the Orange chicken, and the alvacado/cucumber rolls.  We all thought it was the best food we had had in a long time.  Wait staff was friendly and the prices were mid range.  We will come here again for sure when we are in the area!

data.title: GREAT for Lunch!
data.text: I've started going here maybe twice a month for lunch- I live and work in Eau Claire and this place has the best lunch!  You can get two sushi rolls plus soup or salad for $9.00, three sushi rolls plus soup or salad for $12.00!  I recommend choosing the salad over the soup, though... the miso here is not good... but the salad with that ginger dressing they use is so good and my favorite part of my meal here every time!  So worth it though- two people can eat an amazing lunch here for $20!  Dinner is a little more spendy- I came for dinner once and had hibachi- it was mid-range priced, but wasn't quite as good as I'd hoped.  If you want hibachi, go to Fuji... but the sushi here is always good!

data.title: Lunch with friends
data.text: I went with 8 others for lunch and everyone was pleasantly surprised by the atmosphere and the food. We will definitely be going back.

data.title: As good as our local sushi place
data.text: We stopped here for lunch while we were visiting downtown.  We ordered gyoza, snow crab roll, and avocado/peanut roll (rolls came with soup).  All were tasty and reasonably priced.  The waitstaff was friendly and helpful. My only complaint is that they don't sell the awesome Ninja t-shirts that the servers wear.

data.title: Our favorite Asian anywhere!
data.text:
This place is hands-down the best sushi, stirfry, Asian cuisine restaurant in Eau Claire. Situated downtown, it's newly remodeled and the food is simply fantastic.

We have been here multiple times and everything from the appetizers to the sushi to the stir fries to the Japanese inspired Teppanyaki dishes are very very well put together.

Our 26 year old son who lives in Minneapolis says it is their favorite both for price and quality and they are sushi aficionados! We come here whenever we are in Eau Claire, and they have amazingly priced lunch specials.

data.title: Lunch extraordinary!
data.text:
Delicious lunch of California roll and tempura shrimp roll!  My husband had Mongolian beef which he loved!

Fresh meats, vegetables and shrimp! Tempura batter to light and crunchy.  Sauces light and not heavy.  

Wait staff friendly and professional!
Decor modern, minimalist and inviting!

data.title: Nice New Place
data.text: My family has went to Ninja restaurant a couple times.  This is a new restaurant in downtown Eau Claire on Barstow.  The restaurant has a nice decor & is clean.  Service has been great.  We enjoyed our appetizers & main course.  No complaints on food.

data.title: Ick
data.text: The drinks....ugh...like rubbing alcohol! Terrible. The sushi, amazing. The main coarse, it was edible. I would go back for sushi only.

data.title: Mixed
data.text: We shared a veggie tempura sushi appetizer that was fresh, delicious, beautiful.  Then ordered two stir fries.  They were happy to sub tofu for one.  Shrimp stir fry arrived in a timely manner but the veggie one came 20 mins or more later.  Thought they misunderstood or forgot.  Was starving at that point so we shared the first to arrive, with me picking out shrimp.  Waitress was very apologetic.   Seems another table had long wait or problem order.  We ended up taking the second entree to go. It was just ok, have had better prepared tofu.  Got impression the issue was in the kitchen, but also seemed wait staff has some difficulty with language. Will try again. Nice modern Asian decor.

data.title: Fantastic
data.text: Ninja is a new restaurant downtown Eau Claire near the new Lismore Hotel and the beautiful Phoenix Park. It offers awesome sushi bar and an attractive cocktail bar. The menu is extensive - the Teriyaki I ordered was superb. It arrived on a sizzling griddle to start an awesome dining experience!!

data.title: Highly recommended
data.text: My wife and I have eaten here seven times since it opened on Barstow St. We have had an opportunity to try several different appetizers, rolls, stir fries and entrees; as well as cocktails and beer.We have enjoyed everything, and enjoyed every meal. The staff have been friendly, quick and accurate in our orders. The prices are amazingly low - especially at lunch where you can get a salad and two rolls for $9.00; a pot of tea is $1.00. I really like the decor of the restaurant which is modern and trendy, yet cozy and comfortable in the booths. I highly recommend this restaurant; I will be back many times. This may not be a "five star restaurant", but for the kind of restaurant it means to be, it succeeds on all counts.

data.title: Ask what they make in house
data.text:
Many items (what they weren't out of) tasted like they were from a food distributor.  They were pedestrian and not worth eating.  BUT, the two items that we ordered that were made in house were absolutely perfectly prepared and delicious.

They also wouldn't make changes for vegetarians.  How hard can it be, unless you buy prepackaged items off a truck?

Decor is very Chinese and service was good.
